kieran oberman pgj center on democracy development and the rule of law program on global justice stanford university fsi centers & programs research centers center on democracy development and the rule of law center for international security and cooperation center on food security and the environment stanford health policy the europe center walter h shorenstein asia pacific research center research programs program on energy and sustainable development rural education action program educational programs stanford program on international and cross cultural education inter university center for japanese language studies ford dorsey program in international policy studies affiliated programs center for innovation in global health research by topic by region publications people events upcoming recent with papers podcasts & video news recent archive around the web about pgj about the program annual report map & directions contact us about fsi support fsi quick links podcasts & video program on global justice center for ethics in society postdoctoral fellowship project just supply chains people magnify kieran oberman pgj fellow 2009 2011 former program on global justice 616 serra st encina hall stanford ca 94305 6055 kieran stanford edu 650 723 0145 voice research interests immigration restrictions treatment of migrants ethics of immigration policy kieran oberman completed his phd at oxford university his thesis immigration and freedom of movement argued that people have a human right to freedom of movement that entails a right to cross international borders he thus concluded that immigration restrictions could not be justified outside of emergency situations in his post doctoral workat stanford where he divides his time between the program on global justice and the center for ethics in society kieran is continuing to focus on the ethical issues surrounding international migration while at stanford he has completed an article immigration global poverty and the right to stay that argues against using migration as a means to address the problem of global poverty the article is forthcoming in political studies he has also written an article that explores the question of whether the brain drain of skilled workers from poor states could justify the imposition of immigration restrictions he is currently working on a publication based upon his dissertation entitled immigration as a human right in the spring kieran will teach a class entitled introduction to global justice the course is designed to encourage students to think critically about some of the most important issues in international politics including global poverty terrorism war development and climate change search pgj recent commentary post doctoral fellows teach global justice class july 21 2010 news news around the web is immigration a basic human right over arizona's immigration law kieran oberman made a case for immigration as a human right at stanford on friday in its ethics at noon lecture series november 1 2010 in patch support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 724 3241 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
